<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1399,313,586]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
The 
<typeStatus box="[245,348,313,339]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[392,574,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis box="[392,574,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[659,716,314,340]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1133,313,339]" name="Colombia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Colombia</collectingCountry>
differ in a number of details, including the distal fore tarsomeres (white in the Colombian specimen, dark in the type) and the colour of the metapleuron and hind coxa (red in the Colombian specimen, black in the type). Both specimens, however, share several distinctive characters, such as the colour of the mid and hind femora, the broad postocellar part of the frontal vitta, a similar pattern of silvery pruinosity on the scutum and a similarly reddish abdominal base. Furthermore, they easily key out together because of the distinctive femoral colour. More specimens of this species (or species group) are needed to clarify what variation is intraspecific and what is interspecific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1399,625,757]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
This is one of the five species originally described in 
<taxonomicName box="[812,952,626,651]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[812,952,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
solely on the basis of specimens from Callanga, 
<collectingCountry box="[308,366,661,687]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Two remain known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[775,841,661,687]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">types</typeStatus>
. The other three, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1044,1223,660,686]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1223,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<treatmentCitation accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="albimanus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="M. albimanus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1398,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. albimanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[189,383,696,722]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
and 
<treatmentCitation accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[452,795,696,722]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="infestus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="M. infestus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[452,795,696,722]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infestus">
<emphasis box="[452,588,696,722]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. infestus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[601,795,696,722]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
present similar problems because of differences between the Callanga material and putatively conspecific material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1034,1154,731,757]" name="Colombia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1399,796,893]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,476,796,822]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis box="[189,476,796,822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Mesoconius obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual because the absence of a postocellar bristle places it in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1293,1399,797,822]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eques">
<emphasis box="[1293,1399,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. eques</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but the relatively flat katatergite and the spermathecal complex resemble those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1279,1399,831,857]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis box="[1279,1399,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
